What you need to know:

The former Boca Juniors, Barcelona and Napoli star was suffering from liver, kidney and cardiovascular disorders when he died.  Maradona is an idol to millions of Argentines after he inspired the South American country to only their second World Cup triumph in 1986.  His death shocked fans around the world, and tens of thousands queued to file past his coffin, draped in the Argentine flag, at the presidential palace in Buenos Aires amid three days of national mourning.